c. Operating Procedures 

Clearly written safe work practices and operating procedures, especially for high-risk critical tasks, are important for the safe operation of the facility and to reduce the likelihood of a release of hazardous chemicals or energy that could impact employees, the community or the environment. RI-102, "Procedures for Instructions, Standards, and Manuals," RI-124, "Requirements for Operations Work Instructions" and The Electronic Operating Manual (EOM) Guidebook ensure that operating procedures and safe work practices are consistent and accurate.  These practices and procedures were developed in accordance with Section 2760.3 of the Cal/ARP regulation.



Safe Work Practices include, but are not limited to:

- Hot Work (RI-341)

- Control of Entry Into Process Areas (RI-375)

- Control of Hazardous Energy (RI-9900) (includes lockout/tagout and lines/equipment opening)

- General Procedures for Entering/Working in Confined Spaces (RI-9920)



Electronic copies of operating procedures are available to all employees. Paper copies of emergency operating procedures are available in the control room of each process unit.



