The written employee participation plan and facility policies ensure that:



Refinery workers and their representatives are consulted on the conduct and development of PHAs conducted to comply with Section 2760.2 of the Cal/ARP regulation. The Refinery requires participation by plant operations and engineering personnel as members of the analysis team. Other employees with responsibilities relating to specific processes are consulted prior to and during the PHA. Employee involvement is documented in PHA reports.  PHA findings are communicated to affected employees and are available to any employee through the refinery intranet.



Refinery workers and their representatives are consulted on the development of all elements of the process safety program and the emergency response program. Examples of participation include the following:

- Operations and maintenance employees actively review all of the procedures in the EOM (Electronic Operations Manual) and EMM (Electronic Maintenance Manual), and their participation is documented in the Electronic Manuals and Management System (EMMS);

- Employees have active involvement in periodic hands on emergency drills as well as conduct critique sessions, direct involvement in emergency procedure development, consultation in refinery wide emergency plans;

- Operations and maintenance employees are integral members of the required incident investigation teams, and their participation is documented in the incident report;

- Operations and maintenance employees are consulted regarding the development, ongoing improvement, appropriate type and frequency of training; 

